    "description": {
      "content": "OAuth 2.0 client-credentials, refresh, and delegated authorization-grant endpoints that gate every Tink data, payments, and reporting API. Tink issues client access tokens for server-to-server calls, user access tokens on behalf of an end user, and short-lived authorization codes that the Tink Link flow exchanges for user tokens. All other Tink APIs require a Bearer token issued by this service.\n\n\nContact Support:\n Name: Tink Developer Support",
